{"Narrator": """Lucia's hand tightens on her compass, but she keeps working, head down."""},
{"Giovanni": """If you have an accusation to make, Marco, make it directly."""},
{"Marco": """No accusation. Merely concern for an old friend whose work has suddenly become so... precise. So innovative. Almost as if a different hand holds the brush."""},
{"Lorenzo": """Master Marco, I assure you—"""},
{"Marco": """And who is this apprentice? I don't recall approval for a new one."""},
{"Lucia": """I'm nobody. Just helping with preparations."""},
{"Marco": """Nobody? Yet you work at the master's own design table."""},
{"Narrator": """Marco moves closer to the table, examining the drawings. His eyes narrow at the mathematical notations in the margins."""},
{"Marco": """These calculations. This is della Francesca's influence. Since when does a glass painter need mathematics?"""},
{"Giovanni": """The Medici chapel demands new techniques. Surely the guild doesn't oppose innovation?"""},
{"Marco": """Innovation is one thing. Deception is another."""},
{"Narrator": """Marco's hand falls heavily on the design table, inches from Lucia's work."""},
{"Marco": """The guild masters will inspect this workshop tomorrow at noon. I expect to see you personally at work, Giovanni. Demonstrating your... innovations."""},
{"Giovanni": """We will be ready."""},
{"Marco": """For your sake, I hope so. The penalty for guild fraud is more than just a fine, old friend. Much more."""},
{"Narrator": """The workshop door slams behind Marco, rattling the glass panels in their frames."""},
{"Lorenzo": """Tomorrow? It's impossible! Father can barely hold a brush steady enough to—"""},
{"Lucia": """Be quiet and listen. Lorenzo, gather every completed panel and hide them in the cellar. Father, we need to prepare your hands. I'll mix a potion of chamomile and willow bark—it might steady the tremors for a few hours."""},
{"Giovanni": """It won't be enough. My eyes—"""},
{"Lucia": """Then I'll guide your hands. We've done it before. The guild masters will see exactly what they expect to see: the great Giovanni di Salvatore at work."""},
{"Lorenzo": """And if they don't believe it?"""},
{"Lucia": """Then we'd better work through the night preparing a performance they'll have to believe."""},
{"Narrator": """Noon approaches. The workshop has been transformed - every surface gleams, tools perfectly arranged, panels displayed to their best advantage. Giovanni sits at the workbench, Lucia standing close behind him."""},
{"Lucia": """Remember, Father - when they enter, you'll be working on the angel's wing. I've already traced the basic lines. Just follow the patterns beneath your fingers."""},
{"Giovanni": """My hands won't stop shaking."""},
{"Lucia": """They will. The medicine is starting to work. Lorenzo, how do we look from the door?"""},
{"Lorenzo": """Like any other day in the workshop. Though these calculations should be hidden."""},
{"Piero": """Leave them. If anyone questions them, I'll explain their necessity."""},
{"Narrator": """Everyone startles at Piero's voice as he emerges from the back room."""},
{"Lorenzo": """Della Francesca! What are you doing here?"""},
{"Piero": """Providing mathematical consultation on perspective for the Medici windows. A perfectly reasonable activity for a master painter, wouldn't you agree?"""},
{"Lucia": """You don't have to do this."""},
{"Piero": """Consider it an investment in the future of art. Now, Giovanni, let's review these angle calculations before-"""},
{"Narrator": """Heavy footsteps on the stairs interrupt him. The guild masters have arrived."""},
{"Marco": """Ah, Maestro della Francesca. I wasn't expecting to find you here."""},
{"Piero": """The Medici commission demands the finest minds in Florence working together. Surely the guild approves of collaboration between masters?"""},
{"GuildMaster": """Indeed. Though we're more interested in seeing Maestro Giovanni's own work today."""},
{"Narrator": """Giovanni's hand trembles slightly as he lifts the brush. Lucia steps forward, as if to steady him, but Piero catches her arm."""},
{"Piero": """Watch carefully, Masters. You're about to witness something extraordinary."""},
{"Narrator": """Giovanni dips the brush in paint, and for a moment, time seems to stop. Then his hand moves across the glass in one perfect, sweeping stroke."""},
{"GuildMaster": """Remarkable control. The years haven't diminished your skill at all, Giovanni."""},
{"Marco": """Yet the style is so different from your earlier work."""},
{"Giovanni": """An artist must grow, must he not? Della Francesca here has shown me how mathematics can perfect our ancient craft."""},
{"Piero": """The principles of perspective apply to all visual arts. Giovanni has merely adapted them brilliantly to glass."""},
{"Narrator": """The guild masters lean in close, examining the work. Lucia holds her breath."""},
{"GuildMaster": """Well, Marco, are you satisfied? Clearly your concerns were unfounded."""},
{"Marco": """Perhaps. Though I still wonder about this mathematical approach. It seems too... precise for traditional craftsmanship."""},
{"Piero": """Would you prefer imprecision in a Medici commission? Come, let me show you the calculations. Even a guild master might learn something new today."""}
